## Build scand
1. Get AOSP sources
2. Setup your environment (see below for Ubuntu 9.10)
3. link scand in the sources: ln -s /path/to/networkdiscovery/jni /path/to/aosp/frameworks/base/cmds/scand
4. cd /path/to/aosp; . build/envsetup.sh
5. make scand

## Build under Ubuntu 9.10 with Java 5

1. add jaunty repo to /etc/apt/sources.list
  deb http://us.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ jaunty main restricted universe multiverse
  deb-src http://us.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ jaunty main restricted universe multiverse
  
2. Update and Install java 5
  sudo apt-get update & sudo apt-get install sun-java5-jdk
  
3. Use java 5
  sudo update-java-alternatives -s java-1.5.0-sun
  
4. Comment jaunty repo in your sources.list
5. Follow instructions according to your arch
  http://source.android.com/download#TOC-Setting-up-your-machine